==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From mediaeval Latin ''[[almucantarath]]'' or French ''[[almicantarat]]'', from Arabic {{ARchar|المقنطرات}} (al-muqanŧarāt) ‘circles of celestial latitude’, formed from the plural of {{ARchar|[[قنطرة]]}} (qanŧara) ‘arch’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ælmə'kæntə/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#{{archaic}} a [[small circle]] on the [[celestial sphere]], parallel to the [[horizon]], that is used in astronomy and navigation to show [[altitude]] of a star or any other heavenly body.

